# triary — Cursor rules

A workout-logging and scoring PWA. Read `CLAUDE.md` for the full project
guide. This file is the always-on context Cursor should respect.

## Stack

- Backend: Rust 2024 + Axum 0.8 + sqlx + MySQL 8.0 (`backend/`)
- Frontend: TypeScript + SolidJS + TanStack Query + Tailwind + CSS Modules,
  PWA (`frontend/`)
- API: schema first via `openapi/openapi.yaml`
- Migrations: plain SQL via sqlx-cli (no ORM model generation)
- Frontend lint/format: Biome only
- Integration tests: Postman / Newman

## Backend layer rules (hard constraints)

- `backend/src/domain/` MUST NOT import `axum`, `sqlx`, `tower*`,
  `tower_http`, or `tracing`.
- `backend/src/application/` MUST NOT import infrastructure crates.
- Repository traits live in `application/ports/`; implementations in
  `infrastructure/repositories/`.
- `Clock`, `PasswordHasher`, and other "real-world concept" ports live in
  `domain/`.
- `sqlx::FromRow`-derived types stay in `infrastructure/`. They MUST NOT
  appear in `domain` or `application` function signatures.

## Vocabulary rules (anywhere)

- Banned structural names in any layer: `Service`, `Manager`, `Helper`,
  `Util`, `Utils`, `Processor`, `Worker`, `Engine`.
- `Handler` is permitted only inside `interfaces::http`.
- Names must pass the "verb + object responsibility in one sentence" test.

## Coding conventions

- TDD: write the failing test first. Use `proptest` / `@fast-check/vitest`
  for property-based tests where applicable.
- Validators return `Result<T, Vec<DomainError>>` (collected errors).
- API errors come back as `errors[]` arrays, never `{error: {...}}`.
- HTTP status reserved for protocol concerns; domain rule violations are
  always HTTP 400 with a domain-specific `code` in the body.
- IDs at the API boundary are `{prefix}_{ulid}` strings (`usr_`, `exr_`,
  `ses_`, `blk_`, `set_`).
- `panic!` and unchecked exceptions are reserved for programmer bugs only.
- Frontend state: discriminated unions over flag soup. State lives outside
  presentational components; presentational components have no side effects.
- Function nesting <= 3, function length <= 50 lines as the default.

## Quality gates before committing

- Backend: `cargo fmt --all -- --check`, `cargo clippy --all-targets`,
  `cargo nextest run`
- Frontend: `pnpm run lint:ci`, `pnpm run typecheck`, `pnpm run test:run`,
  `pnpm run arch:test`

## Commit message format

Prefix one of: `[feat]` `[fix]` `[update]` `[improve]` `[refactor]`
`[chore]` `[docs]` `[test]` `[style]`. One commit, one purpose.

## Authoritative references

- `.contexts/architecture.md` — layer / aggregate / ADR
- `.contexts/api-design.md` — HTTP API contract
- `.contexts/data-model.md` — DB schema and ID strategy
- `.contexts/specification.md` — user stories
- `openapi/openapi.yaml` — API source of truth
